obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (91515)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892&sectionId=91515&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Public Examinations`
  line `(Prevention of Unfair Means) Act, 2024.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 21st June, 2024, vide notification NO. S.O. 2422(E), dated 21st June, 2024, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (91516)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892&sectionId=91516&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "candidate" means a person who has been granted permission by the public examination`
  line `authority to appear in public examination and includes a person authorised to act as a scribe on his`
  line `behalf in the public examination;`
  line
  line `(b) "communication device" shall have the same meaning assigned to it in clause (ha) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Information Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000);`
  line
  line `(c) "competent authority" shall mean the Ministry or a Department of the Central Government`
  line `administratively concerned with the public examination authority;`
  line
  line `(d) "computer network", "computer resource" and "computer system" shall have the`
  line `meanings respectively assigned to them in clauses (j), (k) and (l) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of`
  line `the Information Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000);`
  line
  line `(e) "conduct of public examination" shall include all the procedures, processes and activities,`
  line `as may be prescribed, for being adopted for the conduct of public examination;`
  line
  line `(f) "institution" means any agency, organisation, body, association of persons, business entity,`
  line `company, partnership or single proprietorship firm, by whatever name it may be called, which is`
  line `other than the public examination authority and the service provider engaged by such authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, it is clarified that "company" includes a company`
  line `as defined in clause (20) of section 2 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2003); or a limited liability`
  line `partnership firm as defined in clause (n) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Limited Liability`
  line `Partnership Act, 2008 (7 of 2009);`
  line
  line `(g)"notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette and the expression`
  line `"notify" shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(h) "organised crime" means an unlawful activity committed by a person or a group of`
  line `persons indulging in unfair means in collusion and conspiracy to pursue or promote a shared`
  line `interest for wrongful gain in respect of a public examination;`
  line
  line `(i) "person associated with a service provider" means a person who performs services for or`
  line `on behalf of such service provider irrespective of whether such person is an employee or an agent`
  line `or a subsidiary of such service provider, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(j) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(k) "public examination" means any examination conducted by the public examination`
  line `authority, as specified in the Schedule, or conducted by such other authority as may be notified by`
  line `the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(l) "public examination authority" means an authority as specified by the Central Government`
  line `by a notification, from time to time for conducting the public examinations;`
  line
  line `(m) "public examination centre" means such premises, which is selected by the service`
  line `provider or otherwise selected by the public examination authority, to be used for conduct of`
  line `public examination and which, amongst others, may include any school, computer centre,`
  line `institution, any building or part thereof and the same shall include the entire periphery and land`
  line `appurtenant thereto which may be used for security and other related reasons for conduct of the`
  line `public examinations; and`
  line
  line `(n)"service provider" means any agency, organisation, body, association of persons, business`
  line `entity, company, partnership or single proprietorship firm, including its associates, subcontractors and provider of support of any computer resource or any material, by whatever name`
  line `it may be called, which is engaged by the public examination authority for conduct of public`
  line examination.
  line
  line `(2) Words and expressions used herein but not defined and defined under any other law for the`
  line `time being in force, shall have the same meanings as assigned to them in those laws.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (91517)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Unfair means.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892&sectionId=91517&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The unfair means relating to the conduct of a public examination shall include`
  line `any act or omission done or caused to be done by any person or group of persons or institutions, and`
  line `include but not be restricted to, any of the following acts for monetary or wrongful gain---`
  line
  line `(i) leakage of question paper or answer key or part thereof;`
  line
  line `(ii) participating in collusion with others to effect leakage of question paper or answer key;`
  line
  line `(iii) accessing or taking possession of question paper or an Optical Mark Recognition`
  line `response sheet without authority;`
  line
  line `(iv) providing solution to one or more questions by any unauthorised person during a public`
  line examination;
  line
  line `(v) directly or indirectly assisting the candidate in any manner unauthorisedly in the public`
  line examination;
  line
  line `(vi) tampering with answer sheets including Optical Mark Recognition response sheets;`
  line
  line `(vii) altering the assessment except to correct a bona fide error without any authority;`
  line
  line `(viii) willful violation of norms or standards set up by the Central Government for conduct of`
  line `a public examination on its own or through its agency;`
  line
  line `(ix) tampering with any document necessary for short-listing of candidates or finalising the`
  line `merit or rank of a candidate in a public examination;`
  line
  line `(x) deliberate violation of security measures to facilitate unfair means in conduct of a public`
  line examination;
  line
  line `(xi) tampering with the computer network or a computer resource or a computer system;`
  line
  line `(xii) manipulation in seating arrangements, allocation of dates and shifts for the candidates to`
  line `facilitate adopting unfair means in examinations;`
  line
  line `(xiii) threatening the life, liberty or wrongfully restraining persons associated with the public`
  line `examination authority or the service provider or any authorised agency of the Government; or`
  line `obstructing the conduct of a public examination;`
  line
  line `(xiv) creation of fake website to cheat or for monetary gain; and`
  line
  line `(xv) conduct of fake examination, issuance of fake admit cards or offer letters to cheat or for`
  line `monetary gain.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (91518)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Conspiracy for unfair means.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892&sectionId=91518&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `No person or group of persons or institutions shall collude or`
  line `conspire to facilitate indulgence in any such unfair means.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (91519)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Disruption to conduct public examination.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892&sectionId=91519&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person, who is not entrusted or engaged`
  line `with the work pertaining to the public examination or conduct of public examination or who is not a`
  line `candidate, shall enter the premises of the examination centre, with intent to disrupt the conduct of the`
  line `public examination.`
  line
  line `(2) No person authorised, engaged or entrusted with the duties to conduct public examination`
  line `shall, before the time fixed for opening and distribution of question papers––`
  line
  line `(a) open, leak or possess or access or solve or seek assistance to solve such question paper or any`
  line `portion or a copy thereof in unauthorised manner for monetary or wrongful gain;`
  line
  line `(b) give any confidential information or promise to give such confidential information to any`
  line `person, where such confidential information is related to or in reference to such question paper for`
  line `monetary or wrongful gain.`
  line
  line `(3) No person, who is entrusted or engaged with any work pertaining to public examination shall,`
  line `except where he is authorised in furtherance of his duties so to do, reveal or cause to be revealed or`
  line `make known to any other person any information or part thereof which has come to his knowledge for`
  line `any undue advantage or wrongful gain.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (91520)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Other offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892&sectionId=91520&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `If any person or group of persons or institution commits any unfair means or`
  line `offence under sections 3, 4 and section 5, the service provider shall forthwith report the offence to the`
  line `concerned police authorities and also inform the public examination authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the service provider resorts to unfair means and commits the offence or is`
  line `involved in facilitating an offence, the public examination authority shall report the same to the`
  line `concerned police authorities.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (91521)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `No premises other than examination centre shall be used for public examination.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892&sectionId=91521&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `It shall`
  line `be an offence for the service provider or any person associated with the service provider to cause any`
  line `premises, other than the examination centre, authorised by the public examination authority, to be`
  line `alternatively used for the purpose of holding public examination, without the written approval of the`
  line `public examination authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall be an offence where any change in the`
  line `examination centre without prior consent of the public examination authority is due to any force`
  line majeure.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (91522)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Offences in respect of service providers and other persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892&sectionId=91522&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person, including the`
  line `person associated with a service provider, shall be deemed to have committed an offence if he`
  line `individually or in collusion with any other person or group of persons or institutions assists any`
  line `person or group of persons or institutions in any manner unauthorisedly in the conduct of public`
  line examination.
  line
  line `(2) Service provider or any person associated with it shall be deemed to have committed an`
  line `offence if he fails to report incidence of any unfair means or commission of any offence.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an offence committed by a service provider is, prima facie, established during`
  line `investigation to have been committed with the consent or connivance of any director, manager, secretary or other officer of such service provider, such person shall also be liable to be proceeded`
  line `against:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment under the Act, if he proves, that the offence was committed without his knowledge and`
  line `that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (91523)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Cognizable offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892&sectionId=91523&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `All offences under this Act, shall be cognizable, non-bailable and`
  line non-compoundable.
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (91524)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Punishment for offences under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892&sectionId=91524&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person or persons resorting to unfair`
  line `means and offences under this Act, shall be punished with imprisonment for a term not less than three`
  line `years but which may extend to five years and with fine up to ten lakh rupees. In case of default of`
  line `payment of fine, an additional punishment of imprisonment shall be imposed, as per the provisions of`
  line `the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023):`
  line
  line `Provided that until the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023) is brought into force, the`
  line `provisions of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), shall be applicable in place of the said Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The service provider shall also be liable to be punished with imposition of a fine upto one`
  line `crore rupees and proportionate cost of examination shall also be recovered from such service provider`
  line `and he shall also be barred from being assigned with any responsibility for the conduct of any public`
  line `examination for a period of four years.`
  line
  line `(3) Where it is established during the investigation that offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed with the consent or connivance of any Director, Senior Management or the persons incharge of the service provider firm, he shall be liable for imprisonment for a term not less than three`
  line `years but which may extend to ten years and with fine of one crore rupees. In case of default of`
  line `payment of fine, an additional punishment of imprisonment shall be imposed as per the provisions of`
  line `the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023):`
  line
  line `Provided that until the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023) is brought into force, the`
  line `provisions of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), shall be applicable in place of the said Act.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing contained in this section shall render any such person liable to any punishment under`
  line `the Act, if he proves, that the offence was committed without his knowledge and that he exercised all`
  line `due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (91525)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Organised crimes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892&sectionId=91525&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a person or a group of persons including the examination authority`
  line `or service provider or any other institution commits an organised crime, he shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment for a term not less than five years but which may extend to ten years and with fine`
  line `which shall not be less than one crore rupees. In case of default of payment of fine, an additional`
  line `punishment of imprisonment shall be imposed as per the provisions of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita,`
  line `2023 (45 of 2023):`
  line
  line `Provided that until the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023) is brought into force, the provisions`
  line `of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), shall be applicable in place of the said Act.`
  line
  line `(2) If an institution is involved in committing an organised crime, its property shall be subjected`
  line `to attachment and forfeiture and proportionate cost of examination shall also be recovered from it.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (91526)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Officers empowered to investigate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892&sectionId=91526&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) An officer not below the rank of Deputy`
  line `Superintendent of Police or Assistant Commissioner of Police shall investigate any offence under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Central Government shall have the`
  line `powers to refer the investigation to any Central Investigating Agency.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (91527)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Members, officers and employees of public examination authority to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892&sectionId=91527&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson, Members, officers and other employees of the public examination`
  line `authority shall be deemed, when acting or purporting to act in pursuance of any of the provisions of`
  line `this Act, to be public servants within the meaning of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023):`
  line
  line `Provided that until the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023) is brought into force, the`
  line `provisions of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), shall be applicable in place of the said Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (91528)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith by any public servant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892&sectionId=91528&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or`
  line `other legal proceedings under this Act, shall lie against any public servant, in respect of anything`
  line `which is done in good faith or intended to be done in the discharge of his official functions or in`
  line `exercise of his powers:`
  line
  line `Provided that the public servants in the service of any public examination authority shall be`
  line `subject to administrative action in terms of service rules of such public examination authority:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing shall prevent proceeding against such public servants where, prima`
  line `facie case exists for establishing commission of an offence under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (91529)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Provisions of this Act to be in addition to other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892&sectionId=91529&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be`
  line `in addition to, and not in derogation of, any other law for the time being in force:`
  line
  line `Provided that the provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent`
  line `therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force or any instrument having effect by`
  line `virtue of any such law in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (91530)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892&sectionId=91530&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:––`
  line
  line `(a) to lay down procedures, processes and activities for being adopted for conduct of the`
  line `public examination;`
  line
  line `(b) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (91531)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Laying of rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892&sectionId=91531&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of`
  line `the session, immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree`
  line `in making any modification in the rule, or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule`
  line `shall, thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so,`
  line `however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (91532)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892&sectionId=91532&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official Gazette, make such`
  line `provisions within three years, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as appear to it to be`
  line `necessary for removal of difficulty.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (91533)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Amendment of Ordinance 38 of 1944.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892&sectionId=91533&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00009_A2024-01_1719556801892
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `In the Criminal Law (Amendment) Ordinance,`
  line `1944, in the Schedule, after serial number 5 and entries relating thereto, the following serial number`
  line `and entries shall be inserted, namely:––`
  line
  line `"6. An offence punishable under the Public Examinations (Prevention of Unfair Means) Act,`
  line `2024.".`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
